    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# A bivariate chi-square test is a statistical method used to determine if a significant association exists between two categorical variables.\n",
        "# It compares observed frequencies in a contingency table to expected frequencies, where a low p-value indicates a statistically significant relationship.\n",
        "\n",
        "import scipy.stats as stats\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Relation between promotion and seasonal\n",
        "observed = pd.crosstab(data['Promotion'], data['Seasonal'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform the Chi-Square test\n",
        "chi2, p, dof, expected = stats.chi2_contingency(observed)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Chi-squared test results:\")\n",
        "print(f\"Chi-square:\", chi2, \", P-value:\", p)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Interpretation\n",
        "if p <= 0.05:\n",
        "    print(\"Reject H0: Variables are dependent.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"Fail to reject H0: Variables are independent.\")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "lf46QMREGR1U",
        "outputId": "b19b35b3-84a5-4142-f13a-165b7bfbc8ce"
      },
      "execution_count": 55,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Chi-squared test results:\n",
            "Chi-square: 0.0 , P-value: 1.0\n",
            "Fail to reject H0: Variables are independent.\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Insights:\n",
        "\n",
        "Since the p-value: 1 > 0.05 with chi-square value: 0, variables are independent of each other （獨立性）\n",
        "\n",
        "The results of the chi-squared test do not allow us to conclude that there is a relationship between promotion and seasonality. In other words, promotion of the products does not depend on whether it is part of a seasonal collection."
